==Old English==
===Etymology===
From [[ge-|ġe-]] + [[frignan|friġnan]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /je'frɪjnan/

===Verb===
'''ġefriġnan''' (class III strong: ''3 singular present'' '''[[gefrigneþ|gefriġneþ]]''', ''3 singular preterite'' '''[[gefrægn|ġefræġn]]''', ''preterite plural'' '''[[gefrugnon|ġefruġnon]]''', ''past participle'' '''[[gefrugnen|ġefruġnen]]''')
# to find out, to hear about, to [[discover]] or [[learn]] something through asking
#:''Ða ic neðan gefrægn hæleþ to hilde'': then I heard that heroes went daringly to war.  (Cædmon's ''Metrical Paraphrase'')

